-- ‚îÄ‚îÄ Microsoft Copilot ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Microsoft's general-purpose consumer AI chat assistant at copilot.microsoft.com, offering conversational answers, image generation, and voice interaction.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Freemium$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(1975, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$220,000+ employees (Microsoft Corporation)$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Redmond, Washington, USA$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$, $q$Spanish$q$, $q$French$q$, $q$German$q$, $q$Portuguese$q$, $q$Chinese$q$, $q$Japanese$q$, $q$Korean$q$, $q$Italian$q$, $q$Dutch$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Microsoft Copilot Review 2026: Features, Pricing and Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Microsoft Copilot review covering free chat, Copilot Pro and Premium tiers, image generation, voice mode, and how it compares to ChatGPT and Gemini.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Microsoft Copilot is Microsoft's consumer-facing conversational AI assistant, accessible at copilot.microsoft.com and built into Windows, Bing, and the Microsoft Start and Edge apps. It traces its lineage to Bing Chat, which launched on February 7, 2023 as part of a major overhaul of the Bing search engine that added a GPT-4-based chatbot to search results. Microsoft rebranded Bing Chat, Windows Copilot, and Microsoft 365 Copilot under the unified Copilot name starting in September 2023, with Bing Chat itself formally renamed Copilot at Microsoft Ignite on November 15, 2023. Microsoft Copilot is distinct from two other Microsoft products that share the Copilot name: Microsoft 365 Copilot, which is embedded inside Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook, and Teams for enterprise productivity and is priced separately as a per-user add-on, and GitHub Copilot, which is a code-completion assistant for developers. The consumer Copilot at copilot.microsoft.com functions as a general-purpose chat assistant: it answers questions, drafts and summarizes text, generates images from text prompts (powered by OpenAI's image models), browses the live web for current information, and offers a voice conversation mode. It is built on OpenAI's GPT model family, with Microsoft periodically adding new capabilities such as Copilot Vision (which can view and discuss on-screen content or camera input) and, in 2026, the option to select Anthropic's Claude as an alternate model within Copilot Chat for tasks like document analysis and structured content generation. The free tier is available to anyone with a Microsoft account and includes standard chat, web-grounded answers, and limited image generation. A paid Copilot Pro subscription at $20 per month offered faster response times, priority access to the latest models, and deeper integration into Microsoft 365 apps for individual subscribers, but Microsoft retired standalone Copilot Pro in late 2025, migrating that functionality into the Microsoft 365 Personal, Family, and Premium subscription tiers instead (existing Copilot Pro subscribers can continue using it until August 1, 2026). Consumer access to advanced Copilot features going forward runs through Microsoft 365 Premium (around $19.99 per month), which folds in the AI capabilities that used to require the standalone Copilot Pro plan. Copilot's target audience spans everyday consumers using it as a free ChatGPT-style assistant, Windows and Edge users who access it natively in the OS and browser, and Microsoft 365 subscribers who want AI assistance woven into their existing apps. Its main competitors are OpenAI's ChatGPT, Google Gemini, and Anthropic's Claude.ai, and its key differentiation is deep, no-extra-app integration into Windows, Bing, and Edge, plus free access without requiring a separate account creation for users already signed into a Microsoft account.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '8439de35-62ee-4d9e-bf6a-d659a4bed51b';

