-- ‚îÄ‚îÄ Microsoft Designer ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$An AI-powered graphic design app from Microsoft that turns text prompts into social posts, presentations, and marketing graphics, positioned as a Canva competitor.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Freemium$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(1975, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$220,000+ employees (Microsoft Corporation)$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Redmond, Washington, USA$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$, $q$Spanish$q$, $q$French$q$, $q$German$q$, $q$Portuguese$q$, $q$Chinese$q$, $q$Japanese$q$, $q$Korean$q$, $q$Italian$q$, $q$Dutch$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Microsoft Designer Review 2026: Features, Pricing and Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Microsoft Designer review covering AI image generation, templates, credits, pricing, and how this Canva competitor fits into Microsoft 365.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Microsoft Designer is an AI-powered graphic design application from Microsoft, publicly previewed on October 12, 2022 alongside the announcement of DALL-E 2 integration into Microsoft's consumer products, and moved to general availability in July 2024. It is Microsoft's direct answer to Canva, letting users generate complete design layouts, including images, text placement, color schemes, and decorative elements, from a plain-language description rather than starting from a blank canvas. Designer's image generation was originally powered by OpenAI's DALL-E 2 and has since been upgraded to DALL-E 3, licensed to Microsoft through its partnership with OpenAI. Beyond generating a design from scratch, Designer offers AI editing tools including background removal, object erase, auto-crop, and Restyle Image, which reimagines an uploaded photo in a new artistic style, plus AI-generated caption and copy suggestions to pair with visuals. It runs as a web app and mobile app, and its generation and editing capabilities are also woven directly into other Microsoft products, including Microsoft Photos, Word, and PowerPoint, so users can create or edit imagery without leaving the app they are already working in. Designer's pricing follows a freemium credit model: the free tier is open to anyone with a Microsoft account and includes a monthly allowance of AI generation credits (around 15 per month), which is sufficient for occasional use but limits heavier design workflows. A Microsoft 365 subscription raises that credit allowance substantially, up to roughly 4x the free amount, and unlocks broader Copilot integration across Microsoft 365 apps; the relevant subscription tiers are Microsoft 365 Personal (around $9.99/month), Family (around $12.99/month), and Premium (around $19.99/month), the last of which also absorbed the features that used to belong to the standalone Copilot Pro subscription. Designer's target audience is primarily small businesses, marketers, students, and social media managers who need quick, on-brand visual content, such as Instagram posts, event invitations, and marketing flyers, without design training or a Canva or Adobe Express subscription. Its main competitors are Canva, Adobe Express, and Adobe Firefly, and its key differentiation is native, no-extra-cost-required integration into the Microsoft 365 ecosystem (PowerPoint, Word, Photos), free access to any Microsoft account holder, and DALL-E 3 image generation baked directly into the design workflow rather than as a bolt-on feature.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '3f7e295f-cbc2-49fa-af99-9d4aa080d1b3';

