-- ‚îÄ‚îÄ Microsoft Entra ID ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Microsoft's cloud-based identity and access management platform, formerly Azure Active Directory, providing single sign-on, multi-factor authentication, and conditional access.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Freemium$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(1975, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$220,000+ employees (Microsoft Corporation)$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Redmond, Washington, USA$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$, $q$Spanish$q$, $q$French$q$, $q$German$q$, $q$Portuguese$q$, $q$Chinese$q$, $q$Japanese$q$, $q$Korean$q$, $q$Italian$q$, $q$Dutch$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Microsoft Entra ID Review 2026: Features, Pricing and Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Microsoft Entra ID review covering Free, P1, P2 and Suite pricing, single sign-on, conditional access, and how it compares to Okta and other IAM tools.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Microsoft Entra ID is Microsoft's cloud-based identity and access management (IAM) platform, previously known as Azure Active Directory (Azure AD). Microsoft announced the rename on July 11, 2023, with the name change rolling out across Microsoft experiences starting August 15, 2023, and most naming updates completing by the end of 2023; Microsoft was explicit that licensing, pricing, and functionality did not change as part of the rebrand, only the name. The underlying service traces back to Windows Server Active Directory concepts from the early 2000s, evolved into the cloud-native Azure Active Directory as part of Microsoft's Azure platform, and is now positioned as the identity layer of the broader Microsoft Entra product family, which also includes tools for permissions management and identity verification. Entra ID works by acting as a centralized cloud directory that authenticates users and enforces access policies across Microsoft 365, Azure, and thousands of third-party SaaS applications through single sign-on (SSO), rather than requiring separate logins per app. Core capabilities include single sign-on, multi-factor authentication (MFA), self-service password reset, and B2B collaboration for inviting external partners into a tenant. Higher tiers add Conditional Access (policies that grant or restrict access based on signals like device, location, and risk level), Identity Protection (machine-learning-based risk detection on sign-ins and accounts that feeds into Conditional Access), Privileged Identity Management or PIM (just-in-time elevation of administrative access instead of standing admin rights), and access reviews for periodic recertification of who has access to what. Pricing is tiered: Entra ID Free is included with any Microsoft online business service and supports up to 500,000 directory objects, SSO for up to 10 cloud apps per user, and basic reports; Entra ID P1 costs roughly $6 to $7 per user per month and adds Conditional Access and hybrid self-service password reset; Entra ID P2 costs roughly $9 to $10 per user per month and adds Identity Protection and PIM; and Microsoft Entra Suite bundles P2 with additional security add-ons for around $12 per user per month. These capabilities are also bundled into Microsoft 365 E3 (which includes P1) and Microsoft 365 E5 (which includes P2), so many enterprise customers already have some tier of Entra ID through their existing Microsoft 365 licensing. Entra ID's target audience is IT and security teams at organizations of any size that need centralized authentication and access control across cloud and on-premises applications, with heavier P1/P2 features aimed at mid-size and enterprise organizations with compliance or zero-trust security requirements. Its main competitors are Okta, Ping Identity, and Google Cloud Identity, and its key differentiation is deep native integration with Microsoft 365, Azure, and Windows, plus inclusion inside existing Microsoft 365 E3/E5 licensing that many enterprises already own.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '71439181-0154-4626-9efe-059864fd8420';

